      "name": "Skill",
      "args": {
        "skill": "stm32agent",
        "args": "Reconnect to the VCP after the target reset."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 vcp reconnect",
        "description": "Force-reconnect to VCP after target reset (VCP-003)"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "This maps directly to **VCP-003** \u2014 force-reconnect after a target reset. Running it now:\nThe reconnect failed \u2014 **COM9 is already held by another process** (PermissionError 13 / Access Denied). The substrate can't open the port until whatever is holding it lets go.\n\n**Fix options:**\n\n1. **Close the competing tool** \u2014 if you have minicom, screen, picocom, Cutecom, STM32CubeIDE's serial monitor, PuTTY, or any other terminal open on COM9, close it and then re-run:\n   ```\n   stm32 vcp reconnect\n   ```\n\n2. **Find the holding process** (Windows) \u2014 run this in a separate terminal to identify it:\n   ```powershell\n   Get-Process | Where-Object { $_.Modules.FileName -match \"COM9\" }\n   ```\n   or use **Resource Monitor \u2192 CPU tab \u2192 search \"COM9\"** in the Associated Handles section.\n\n3. **If the substrate itself is the holder** from a previous session, run `stm32 vcp close` first to release it, then reconnect.\n\nOnce the port is free, `stm32 vcp reconnect` will re-enumerate the probe's CDC interface and latch the connection for subsequent `tail` / `send` calls."
}